<TITLE> New director general appointed for NSI </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 19 (bdnews24.com)  Maj Gen Sheikh Md Monirul Islam has been appointed director general of the National Security Intelligence, a government statement said Saturday. Maj Gen Islam will move from his position as director general of the Special Security Force to take up his new post on Sunday, the statement said. The new NSI director general served as Commanding Officer of the East Bengal Regiment and as General Staff Officer First Grade of an infantry division. He was commissioned in the Bangladesh Army's East Bengal Regiment in 1978. bd
